<div class="container text">
    <h1>Methodology</h1>

    <p>
        ONVX measures the overnight change in implied volatility using a fixed,
        transparent, and repeatable process.
    </p>

    <h3>Underlying</h3>
    <p>
        ONVX is calculated using options on a single underlying equity index proxy.
    </p>

    <h3>Option Selection</h3>
    <p>
        At-the-money call and put options are selected for a fixed maturity.
        Implied volatility is averaged across calls and puts.
    </p>

    <h3>Timing</h3>
    <p>
        Implied volatility is observed shortly before the market close
        and again shortly after the market open.
    </p>

    <h3>Calculation</h3>
    <p>
        ONVX = Implied Volatility (Open) âˆ’ Implied Volatility (Close)
    </p>

    <h3>Principles</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>No forecasts</li>
        <li>No discretionary adjustments</li>
        <li>No revisions to historical values</li>
    </ul>

